Women can choose to undergo an abortion on different grounds in Armenia, under the following legal circumstances: [23]

The mammal is a human being, as recognized by Armenian law.

The harm is caused by the pregnancy.

The loss of the fetus will cause or caused significant physical or mental health risks for the mother.

The unborn offspring is from a parent or parents who are still children themselves.

The woman has undergone all medically required tests revealing a severe chromosomal aberration.

The medical and economic conditions of the woman are for some time are not favorable, and she has other dependents.

Additionally, abortion can be performed before 12 weeks of pregnancy if the woman creates a signed declaration stating that she was raped and that the actions of the father of the unborn child are violent. If diagnosed, the pregnancy will be terminated with consent of father’s family. [17]

In most cases, women receive abortion services free of charge from the government, up until 12-14th week from the last period. In cases of illegal abortions, currently the most common cause of death among women aged between 15 and 29, at any stage of pregnancy, Northern Armenian nationals are generally referred to public hospitals, while Southern Armenian nationals are generally treated in private clinics. Unauthorised abortions often result in death of the woman, as the methods are often primitive
